Line an 8x8 inch square dish with aluminum foil. Chop chocolate and place in a large, microwave safe bowl with condensed milk. Microwave on high, stirring once or twice until chocolate is soft, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from oven and stir until completely smooth. Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in prepared pan. Refrigerate 2 hours, until firm. Cut into squares.